were endangered in Africa and the environment

00:38:42.260 --> 00:38:48.470
was endangered in Africa, it was because of
the way that poor people were having to scrounge

00:38:48.470 --> 00:38:53.050
for food. That they were cutting down the
forest to find any kind of acre land that

00:38:53.050 --> 00:38:57.220
they could plant; that they didn't have the
means to grow enough food on their own land.

00:38:57.220 --> 00:39:01.720
That they had to keep moving after they grow
out in some land and do a bad job of it, exhaust

00:39:01.720 --> 00:39:07.500
the soil, they have to move on to somewhere
else, it's called slash and burn farming.

00:39:07.500 --> 00:39:11.600
A little while after he took this picture,
he was flying in a plane over the, near the

00:39:11.600 --> 00:39:20.200
Serengeti and he was taking pictures of the
thundering herds of the wildebeest and zebra.

00:39:20.200 --> 00:39:24.070
But, on the flight, he noticed the fires in
the distance and they flew over, and they

00:39:24.070 --> 00:39:28.740
realized that the farmers are burning down
the forest to try to make room to grow, and

00:39:28.740 --> 00:39:33.230
the light went off in his head, and he realized
that we can't, you really can't handle the

00:39:33.230 --> 00:39:37.690
conservation issue, you can't make your progress
in conservation unless you help people feed

00:39:37.690 --> 00:39:45.760
themselves. And so, his focus changed from
being primarily, conservationist to being

00:39:45.760 --> 00:39:51.320
someone who wants to help people in Africa
