00:51:08.030 --> 00:51:15.880
The Green Revolution of Asia in 1960s and
1970s isn't what we want and isn't the Green

00:51:15.880 --> 00:51:20.380
Revolution that would work in Africa today
and it's a different Green Revo--different

00:51:20.380 --> 00:51:24.970
Green Revolution. Green Revolution is actually
a very loaded term because it gets associated

00:51:24.970 --> 00:51:29.339
with the heavy use of pesticides and fertilizers.
There was a lot of--when they started it in

00:51:29.339 --> 00:51:35.550
the 1960s and '70s, they didn't know enough--they
didn't as much as they know now. So, what

00:51:35.550 --> 00:51:39.010
had had happened there, you know, farmers
who have been starving one year, they have

00:51:39.010 --> 00:51:44.030
a big crop because they start putting fertilizer
on it. And so, they said, "Gee, that was great,

00:51:44.030 --> 00:51:50.260
more would be better." And they put too much
on, and they got into the water ways. Since

00:51:50.260 --> 00:51:55.339
that time, we've learned a lot more about
how not to waste fertilizer. I mean, the farmers

00:51:55.339 --> 00:51:59.100
quickly realized that, you know, if you put
on too much, you're wasting it, why spend

00:51:59.100 --> 00:52:04.540
that money on it? So, in Africa, we've gotten
to the point now where you--I think you could

00:52:04.540 --> 00:52:08.980
much more micro-manage the amount of fertilizer
and the insecticides that you use, that you

00:52:08.980 --> 00:52:16.550
can avoid those problems or a lot of those
problems. But I also say this that what happened,

00:52:16.550 --> 00:52:23.069
you know, in the 1960s and 1970s, the famine
stopped other than North Korea. You know,

00:52:23.069 --> 00:52:27.650
famine stopped in Asia. If you--if we were
talking about this in 1960s and 1970s, you

00:52:27.650 --> 00:52:31.060
would think that were be the best thing that
could possibly happen. Well, now, in hindsight,

00:52:31.060 --> 00:52:35.000
we can look back and we're not worried about
famine in Asia anymore. So, we can worry about

00:52:35.000 --> 00:52:44.089
things like, "Gee, they were excesses that
occurred. It's--what you're arguing about

00:52:44.089 --> 00:52:51.930
is which is worse, problems of scarcity or
